Sentencas: NiFe2 coating with thickness of 3.5, 6.5 and 9.5 mu m was deposited on SUS 430 steel by magnetron sputtering 2 h, 4 h and 6 h, respectively, for application as protective coating of solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) interconnects.
Titulo: Effect of NiFe2 coating thickness on high temperature oxidation and electrical behavior of coated steel interconnect

Sentencas: Oxidation and electrical behavior of the coated steels were evaluated in air at 800 degrees C for durations of up to 15 weeks to investigate the effect of coating thickness.
Titulo: Effect of NiFe2 coating thickness on high temperature oxidation and electrical behavior of coated steel interconnect

Sentencas: It is found that 4 h and 6 h samples showed better oxidation resistance and Cr-blocking effectiveness compared to 2 h sample.
Titulo: Effect of NiFe2 coating thickness on high temperature oxidation and electrical behavior of coated steel interconnect

Sentencas: The lowest area specific resistance (ASR) after 15-week oxidation was achieved for 4 h sample.
Titulo: Effect of NiFe2 coating thickness on high temperature oxidation and electrical behavior of coated steel interconnect

Sentencas: Results suggest that 6.5 mu m NiFe2 coating of 4 h sample exhibited an appropriate thickness for effectively inhibiting Cr out-diffusion and improving the oxidation resistance while maintaining a low scale ASR.
Titulo: Effect of NiFe2 coating thickness on high temperature oxidation and electrical behavior of coated steel interconnect
